            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20take%20care%20of%20unfinished%20business.%20God%20is%20a%20God%20of%20justice%20and%20cannot%20overlook%20the%20horrible%20reality%20of%20sin.%20Saul%20killed%20people%20with%20whom%20Israel%20had%20pledged%20a%20covenant%20in%20the%20days%20of%20Joshua.%20Though%20Saul%20viewed%20the%20killings%20as%20justifiable%2C%20the%20victims'%20innocent%20blood%20cried%20out%20before%20God%2C%20demanding%20justice.%20The%20heavens%20remained%20as%20brass%20for%20David%20and%20Israel%20until%20they%20dealt%20with%20and%20atoned%20for%20Saul's%20actions.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMany%20things%20occur%20in%20societies%20because%20God%20is%20avenging%20past%20actions%20and%20atrocities%20that%20were%20leveled%20against%20innocent%20people.%20What%20generational%20curses%20have%20fallen%20upon%20our%20cities%20and%20nations%20because%20of%20the%20past%20sins%20of%20our%20fathers%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%202%20Samuel%2024%2C%20we%20see%20that%20God%20was%20so%20serious%20about%20justice%20that%20seventy%20thousand%20people%20died%20to%20appease%20His%20wrath%20(v.%2015).%20We%20must%20be%20serious%20enough%20about%20sins%20against%20others%20to%20cry%20out%20in%20repentance%2C%20approach%20the%20offended%2C%20and%20make%20reconciliation.%20These%20actions%2C%20as%20simple%20as%20they%20may%20seem%2C%20will%20release%20the%20blessing%20of%20God.%20As%20David%20did%2C%20we%20must%20help%20restore%20and%20heal%20the%20breaches%20of%20the%20past%2C%20because%20after%20he%20had%20made%20restitution%2C%20%22the%20Lord%20answered%20his%20prayer%22%20(v.%2025).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
