            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Samuel.20:14-21:22",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Samuel%2020%3A14-21%3A22%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_14%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Sheba%20traveled%20through%20all%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel%20and%20eventually%20came%20to%20the%20town%20of%20Abel-beth-maacah.%20All%20the%20members%20of%20his%20own%20clan%2C%20the%20Bicrites%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20and%20Latin%20versions%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EAll%20the%20Berites.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20assembled%20for%20battle%20and%20followed%20him%20into%20the%20town.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_15%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Joab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20forces%20arrived%2C%20they%20attacked%20Abel-beth-maacah.%20They%20built%20a%20siege%20ramp%20against%20the%20town%26%23x2019%3Bs%20fortifications%20and%20began%20battering%20down%20the%20wall.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_16%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20a%20wise%20woman%20in%20the%20town%20called%20out%20to%20Joab%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen%20to%20me%2C%20Joab.%20Come%20over%20here%20so%20I%20can%20talk%20to%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_17%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20he%20approached%2C%20the%20woman%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAre%20you%20Joab%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ESo%20she%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen%20carefully%20to%20your%20servant.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%26%23x2019%3Bm%20listening%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_18%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20she%20continued%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThere%20used%20to%20be%20a%20saying%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20settle%20an%20argument%2C%20ask%20advice%20at%20the%20town%20of%20Abel.%26%23x2019%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_19%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20am%20one%20who%20is%20peace%20loving%20and%20faithful%20in%20Israel.%20But%20you%20are%20destroying%20an%20important%20town%20in%20Israel.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ea%20town%20that%20is%20a%20mother%20in%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Why%20do%20you%20want%20to%20devour%20what%20belongs%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_20%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20Joab%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBelieve%20me%2C%20I%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20want%20to%20devour%20or%20destroy%20your%20town!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_21%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20not%20my%20purpose.%20All%20I%20want%20is%20a%20man%20named%20Sheba%20son%20of%20Bicri%20from%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim%2C%20who%20has%20revolted%20against%20King%20David.%20If%20you%20hand%20over%20this%20one%20man%20to%20me%2C%20I%20will%20leave%20the%20town%20in%20peace.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BAll%20right%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20woman%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bwe%20will%20throw%20his%20head%20over%20the%20wall%20to%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_22%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20woman%20went%20to%20all%20the%20people%20with%20her%20wise%20advice%2C%20and%20they%20cut%20off%20Sheba%26%23x2019%3Bs%20head%20and%20threw%20it%20out%20to%20Joab.%20So%20he%20blew%20the%20ram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20horn%20and%20called%20his%20troops%20back%20from%20the%20attack.%20They%20all%20returned%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20and%20Joab%20returned%20to%20the%20king%20at%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_23%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20Joab%20was%20the%20commander%20of%20the%20army%20of%20Israel.%20Benaiah%20son%20of%20Jehoiada%20was%20captain%20of%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20bodyguard.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_24%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EAdoniram%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A24%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20(see%20also%201%26%23xA0%3BKgs%204%3A6%3B%205%3A14)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EAdoram.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20forced%20labor.%20Jehoshaphat%20son%20of%20Ahilud%20was%20the%20royal%20historian.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_25%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3ESheva%20was%20the%20court%20secretary.%20Zadok%20and%20Abiathar%20were%20the%20priests.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_20_26%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20Ira%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20Jair%2C%20was%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20personal%20priest.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Avenges%20the%20Gibeonites%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20famine%20during%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20that%20lasted%20for%20three%20years%2C%20so%20David%20asked%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20about%20it.%20And%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20famine%20has%20come%20because%20Saul%20and%20his%20family%20are%20guilty%20of%20murdering%20the%20Gibeonites.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20king%20summoned%20the%20Gibeonites.%20They%20were%20not%20part%20of%20Israel%20but%20were%20all%20that%20was%20left%20of%20the%20nation%20of%20the%20Amorites.%20The%20people%20of%20Israel%20had%20sworn%20not%20to%20kill%20them%2C%20but%20Saul%2C%20in%20his%20zeal%20for%20Israel%20and%20Judah%2C%20had%20tried%20to%20wipe%20them%20out.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20asked%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20can%20I%20do%20for%20you%3F%20How%20can%20I%20make%20amends%20so%20that%20you%20will%20bless%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20people%20again%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWell%2C%20money%20can%26%23x2019%3Bt%20settle%20this%20matter%20between%20us%20and%20the%20family%20of%20Saul%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20Gibeonites%20replied.%20%26%23x201C%3BNeither%20can%20we%20demand%20the%20life%20of%20anyone%20in%20Israel.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20can%20I%20do%20then%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20David%20asked.%20%26%23x201C%3BJust%20tell%20me%20and%20I%20will%20do%20it%20for%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20they%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIt%20was%20Saul%20who%20planned%20to%20destroy%20us%2C%20to%20keep%20us%20from%20having%20any%20place%20at%20all%20in%20the%20territory%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20let%20seven%20of%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20us%2C%20and%20we%20will%20execute%20them%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20Gibeon%2C%20on%20the%20mountain%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E21%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20(see%20also%2021%3A9)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Eat%20Gibeah%20of%20Saul%2C%20the%20chosen%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%20class%3D%22tn-sc-ital%22%3ELord%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BAll%20right%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20king%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20will%20do%20it.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20spared%20Jonathan%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%20Mephibosheth%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E21%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3EMephibosheth%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20another%20name%20for%20Merib-baal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20who%20was%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20grandson%2C%20because%20of%20the%20oath%20David%20and%20Jonathan%20had%20sworn%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20gave%20them%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20two%20sons%20Armoni%20and%20Mephibosheth%2C%20whose%20mother%20was%20Rizpah%20daughter%20of%20Aiah.%20He%20also%20gave%20them%20the%20five%20sons%20of%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughter%20Merab%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E21%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20a%20few%20Hebrew%20and%20Greek%20manuscripts%20and%20Syriac%20version%20(see%20also%201%26%23xA0%3BSam%2018%3A19)%3B%20most%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3EMichal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20wife%20of%20Adriel%20son%20of%20Barzillai%20from%20Meholah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_21_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20men%20of%20Gibeon%20executed%20them%20on%20the%20mountain%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20So%20all%20seven%20of%20them%20died%20together%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20barley%20harvest.%3C%2Fverse_expo